{"type":"message","id":"f0fa5bfa","parentId":"bf781bec","timestamp":"2026-07-02T11:55:30.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Published to LinkedIn:**\n→ https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7478416007905153025/\n\n**Characters:** 958 | **Image:** ✅\n\nThat's post #3. You're back in the game. Want to queue up the next one, or should I check back tomorrow to keep you on track?"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_18e36845348c4ea8b7509187","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 𝗔𝗹𝗲𝘅 𝗞𝗮𝗿𝗽 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-02T11:55:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7478416007905153025/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7478416007905153025\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 958\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/karp-meltdown-1782993194.jpg\n\n## Post Body\n\n𝗔𝗹𝗲𝘅 𝗞𝗮𝗿𝗽 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\nHe had a moment most CEOs will never allow themselves.\n\n20 minutes on live TV.\nStuttering. Tangents. Talking about his parents wanting him to be a professor at Berkeley.\nThe chyron called it a \"televised nervous breakdown.\"\n\nHere's what everyone's missing:\n\nEvery other CEO in AI is polished. Scripted. Focus-grouped.\nKarp went on CNBC and... just talked.\nRanted about AI being oversold.\nComplained about the bubble.\nGot lost in his own thoughts.\n\nWas it messy? Absolutely.\nWas it real? Also yes.\n\nWe've gotten so used to corporate-speak that raw humanity looks like a crisis.\nThe bar for \"breakdown\" is now: showing up without a script and saying what you actually think.\n\nI'm not saying it was good TV.\nI'm saying it was human.\nAnd in a world of AI-generated everything, that might be the rarest thing left.\n\nWhen's the last time you saw a leader drop the mask on camera?\n\n#AI #Leadership #Authenticity #Palantir #AlexKarp\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n","path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-02-alex-karp-didnt-have-a.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# 𝗔𝗹𝗲𝘅 𝗞𝗮𝗿𝗽 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-02T11:55:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7478416007905153025/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7478416007905153025\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 958\\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/karp-meltdown-1782993194.jpg\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\n𝗔𝗹𝗲𝘅 𝗞𝗮𝗿𝗽 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\\nHe had a moment most CEOs will never allow themselves.\\n\\n20 minutes on live TV.\\nStuttering. Tangents. Talking about his parents wanting him to be a professor at Berkeley.\\nThe chyron called it a \\\"televised nervous breakdown.\\\"\\n\\nHere's what everyone's missing:\\n\\nEvery other CEO in AI is polished. Scripted. Focus-grouped.\\nKarp went on CNBC and... just talked.\\nRanted about AI being oversold.\\nComplained about the bubble.\\nGot lost in his own thoughts.\\n\\nWas it messy? Absolutely.\\nWas it real? Also yes.\\n\\nWe've gotten so used to corporate-speak that raw humanity looks like a crisis.\\nThe bar for \\\"breakdown\\\" is now: showing up without a script and saying what you actually think.\\n\\nI'm not saying it was good TV.\\nI'm saying it was human.\\nAnd in a world of AI-generated everything, that might be the rarest thing left.\\n\\nWhen's the last time you saw a leader drop the mask on camera?\\n\\n#AI #Leadership #Authenticity #Palantir #AlexKarp\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\", \"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-02-alex-karp-didnt-have-a.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vert