{"type":"message","id":"6ad6d12b","parentId":"91367dd8","timestamp":"2026-07-02T14:01:10.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_77d81e7712b542d6b92bbc9f","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\n\nHere are 3 posts ready to publish — all based on fresh news from today. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately."},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\\n\\nHere are 3 posts ready to publish — all based on fresh news from today. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6baea8eab29940a1a97cae1a","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗳𝗶𝗴𝘂𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗶𝘁 𝗼𝘂𝘁.\n\nThey cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half — by making AI agents LESS autonomous.\n\nNot more.\nLess.\n\nEveryone's chasing \"fully autonomous agents.\"\nMorgan Stanley went the opposite direction.\nFixed rules. Human sign-off on every call. Fewer probabilistic decisions.\n\nResult?\nThe job that used to break their team is now reliable.\n\nHere's the insight most teams miss:\nAutonomy is a feature for demos.\nControl is a feature for production.\n\nThe companies actually shipping AI agents aren't building self-driving everything.\nThey're building systems that know WHEN to ask for permission.\n\nIf your AI agent can't explain what it's about to do before it does it —\nyou're not ready for production.\nYou're ready for a demo.\n\nWhat's the most fragile process in your business that could use an agent with guardrails?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #Automation #Leadership\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Morgan Stanley cut its riskiest reconciliation job in half (VentureBeat, Jun 30)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-02-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-02-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-02-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆 𝗳𝗶𝗴𝘂𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗶𝘁 𝗼𝘂𝘁.\\n\\nThey cut their riskiest reconciliation job in half — by making AI agents LESS autonomous.\\n\\nNot more.\\nLess.\\n\\nEveryone's chasing \\\"fully autonomous agents.\\\"\\nMorgan Stanley went the opposite direction.\\nFixed rules. Human sign-off on every call. Fewer probabilistic decisions.\\n\\nResult?\\nThe job that used to break their team is now reliable.\\n\\nHere's the insight most teams miss:\\nAutonomy is a feature for demos.\\nControl is a feature for production.\\n\\nThe companies actually shipping AI agents aren't building self-driving everything.\\nThey're building systems that know WHEN to ask for permission.\\n\\nIf your AI agent can't explain what it's about to do before it does it —\\nyou're not ready for production.\\nYou're ready for a demo.\\n\\nWhat's the most fragile process in your business that could use an agent with guardrails?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #Automation #Leadership\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Morgan Stanley cut its riskiest reconciliation job in half (VentureBeat, Jun 30)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-02-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-02-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-02-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3bc03c0ae3914d7aadbacece","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗼𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘄𝗮𝗿 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗰𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗱𝗲𝗱.\n\nZ.ai just launched ZCode.\nNow you've got Cursor. Claude Code. GitHub Copilot. ZCode.\nAll fighting for your terminal.\n\nGood news for developers.\nBad news for anyone who thought this space was settled.\n\nHere's what nobody's talking about:\nEvery new AI coding tool = another integration to manage.\nAnother context window to pay for.\nAnother agent that \"knows\" your codebase... separately.\n\nThe real opportunity isn't picking ONE tool.\nIt's building infrastructure that lets you swap them.\n\nBYOK (bring your own key) is becoming table stakes.\nMulti-model orchestration is next.\nIf your workflow is locked to one vendor, you're not future-proof — you're vendor-hostage.\n\nThe winners won't be the teams with the best AI.\nThey'll be the teams who can swap AIs without breaking everything.\n\nHow many AI tools is too many before you lose control?\n\n#AI #Coding #DeveloperTools #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Z.ai launches ZCode to challenge Cursor, Claude Code and GitHub Copilot (VentureBeat, Jul 2)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-02-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-02-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-02-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗼𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘄𝗮𝗿 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗰𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗱𝗲𝗱.\\n\\nZ.ai just launched ZCode.\\nNow you've got Cursor. Claude Code. GitHub Copilot. ZCode.\\nAll fighting for your terminal.\\n\\nGood news for developers.\\nBad news for anyone who thought this space was settled.\\n\\nHere's what nobody's talking about:\\nEvery new AI coding tool = another integration to manage.\\nAnother context window to pay for.\\nAnother agent that \\\"knows\\\" your codebase... separately.\\n\\nThe real opportunity isn't picking ONE tool.\\nIt's building infrastructure that lets you swap them.\\n\\nBYOK (bring your own key) is becoming table stakes.\\nMulti-model orchestration is next.\\nIf your workflow is locked to one vendor, you're not future-proof — you're vendor-hostage.\\n\\nThe winners won't be the teams with the best AI.\\nThey'll be the teams who can swap AIs without breaking everything.\\n\\nHow many AI tools is too many before you lose control?\\n\\n#AI #Coding #DeveloperTools #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Z.ai launches ZCode to challenge Cursor, Claude Code and GitHub Copilot (VentureBeat, Jul 2)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-02-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-02-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-02-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a74075ab299546a1a570b605","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗔 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗮𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹.\n\nSquare announced restaurants can now accept orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude.\nNo app to build. No integration to code. Just... turn it on.\n\nThis is what AI adoption actually looks like.\nNot a 2-year transformation roadmap.\nA checkbox in your existing dashboard.\n\nThe businesses winning right now aren't reinventing themselves.\nThey're layering AI onto what already works.\n\nYour customers are already talking to ChatGPT.\nNow ChatGPT can talk to your inventory system.\nYour POS.\nYour order flow.\n\nThe question isn't \"How do we build an AI strategy?\"\nThe question is \"Which AI channel is already knocking on our door?\"\n\nIf a local restaurant can accept orders from an LLM by next week —\nwhat's your excuse for still \"exploring\" AI?\n\nWhat's one customer touchpoint in your business that AI should already be handling?\n\n#AI #SmallBusiness #Automation #CustomerExperience #Square\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Restaurants can now accept orders placed directly from ChatGPT and Claude (VentureBeat, Jul 1)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-02-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-02-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-02-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗔 𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗮𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗼𝘁 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗹.\\n\\nSquare announced restaurants can now accept orders directly from ChatGPT and Claude.\\nNo app to build. No integration to code. Just... turn it on.\\n\\nThis is what AI adoption actually looks like.\\nNot a 2-year transformation roadmap.\\nA checkbox in your existing dashboard.\\n\\nThe businesses winning right now aren't reinventing themselves.\\nThey're layering AI onto what already works.\\n\\nYour customers are already talking to ChatGPT.\\nNow ChatGPT can talk to your inventory system.\\nYour POS.\\nYour order flow.\\n\\nThe question isn't \\\"How do we build an AI strategy?\\\"\\nThe question is \\\"Which AI channel is already knocking on our door?\\\"\\n\\nIf a local restaurant can accept orders from an LLM by next week —\\nwhat's your excuse for still \\\"exploring\\\" AI?\\n\\nWhat's one customer touchpoint in your business that AI should already be handling?\\n\\n#AI #SmallBusiness #Automation #CustomerExperience #Square\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Restaurants can now accept orders placed directly from ChatGPT and Claude (VentureBeat, Jul 1)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-02-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-02-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-02-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1d626e6d7cbb4ddb8eb1694a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"touch \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/.brief-sent-2026-07-02\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"touch \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/.brief-sent-2026-07-02\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783000848719,"responseId":"EW9GarrfPNfv6dgPma-DkAM"}}
