{"type":"message","id":"eb408399","parentId":"1a15d53c","timestamp":"2026-07-03T05:14:45.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bafd71547f9a454b825074a9","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\n\nHere are 3 fresh posts for today — all based on the latest news. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately."},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"Good morning, Andrii! ☀️\\n\\nHere are 3 fresh posts for today — all based on the latest news. Tap ✅ to publish any immediately.\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e2243d1304ec4fa1982e3f96","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗧𝘄𝗼-𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗱𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱𝘆 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗖𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗱𝗲 𝗙𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝟱 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\n\nClaude Fable 5 disappeared for a few weeks due to export controls.\nMost enterprises didn't panic.\nBecause they'd already built their hedge.\n\nNew data shows:\n- 66% had backup models ready\n- 79% have already paid for an agent going rogue\n- Only 1 in 10 can automatically catch a failing AI system in production\n\nHere's the uncomfortable truth:\nIf your business depends on ONE model provider —\nyou're not building AI infrastructure.\nYou're building vendor dependency.\n\nThe companies that sailed through the outage?\nThey treated models as swappable from day one.\nThe ones that scrambled?\nThey bet everything on a single API key.\n\nMulti-model isn't a nice-to-have anymore.\nIt's survival.\n\nHow many model providers is your business dependent on right now?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #RiskManagement #AIAgents #Infrastructure\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Enterprises lost Claude Fable 5 for a few weeks (VentureBeat, Jul 3)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-03-1"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-03-1"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-03-1"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗧𝘄𝗼-𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗿𝗱𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱𝘆 𝘄𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗖𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗱𝗲 𝗙𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝟱 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻.\\n\\nClaude Fable 5 disappeared for a few weeks due to export controls.\\nMost enterprises didn't panic.\\nBecause they'd already built their hedge.\\n\\nNew data shows:\\n- 66% had backup models ready\\n- 79% have already paid for an agent going rogue\\n- Only 1 in 10 can automatically catch a failing AI system in production\\n\\nHere's the uncomfortable truth:\\nIf your business depends on ONE model provider —\\nyou're not building AI infrastructure.\\nYou're building vendor dependency.\\n\\nThe companies that sailed through the outage?\\nThey treated models as swappable from day one.\\nThe ones that scrambled?\\nThey bet everything on a single API key.\\n\\nMulti-model isn't a nice-to-have anymore.\\nIt's survival.\\n\\nHow many model providers is your business dependent on right now?\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #RiskManagement #AIAgents #Infrastructure\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Enterprises lost Claude Fable 5 for a few weeks (VentureBeat, Jul 3)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-03-1\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-03-1\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-03-1\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7f15a487a066441c85418775","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗔𝗹𝗶𝗯𝗮𝗯𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗰𝘂𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻 𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟵%.\n\nMost AI agents choke when you hand them thousands of tools.\nThey load EVERYTHING into context.\nBurn through tokens. Get slow. Expensive. Unreliable.\n\nAlibaba's new framework does something different:\nIt skips loading every tool.\n\nInstead of stuffing the entire toolbox into context,\nit routes to the right tool on demand.\nResult? 99% less token waste.\n\nHere's why this matters:\nThe current AI agent trend is \"give it more tools.\"\nMore APIs. More capabilities. More context bloat.\nThat's why your agents are slow and expensive.\n\nThe future isn't more tools in context.\nIt's smarter routing to fewer tools.\n\nIf your agent needs to \"know\" 500 tools to do its job —\nyou've built it wrong.\nYou've built a search engine, not an agent.\n\nWhat's the maximum number of tools an agent should actually have loaded?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Efficiency #Alibaba #TokenOptimization\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: New Alibaba AI framework skips loading every tool (VentureBeat, Jul 2)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-03-2"},"label":"✅ Publish now","style":"success"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-03-2"},"label":"✏️ Edit first"},{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-03-2"},"label":"⏭️ Skip","style":"secondary"}],"type":"buttons"}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗔𝗹𝗶𝗯𝗮𝗯𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗰𝘂𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻 𝘂𝘀𝗲 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟵%.\\n\\nMost AI agents choke when you hand them thousands of tools.\\nThey load EVERYTHING into context.\\nBurn through tokens. Get slow. Expensive. Unreliable.\\n\\nAlibaba's new framework does something different:\\nIt skips loading every tool.\\n\\nInstead of stuffing the entire toolbox into context,\\nit routes to the right tool on demand.\\nResult? 99% less token waste.\\n\\nHere's why this matters:\\nThe current AI agent trend is \\\"give it more tools.\\\"\\nMore APIs. More capabilities. More context bloat.\\nThat's why your agents are slow and expensive.\\n\\nThe future isn't more tools in context.\\nIt's smarter routing to fewer tools.\\n\\nIf your agent needs to \\\"know\\\" 500 tools to do its job —\\nyou've built it wrong.\\nYou've built a search engine, not an agent.\\n\\nWhat's the maximum number of tools an agent should actually have loaded?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Efficiency #Alibaba #TokenOptimization\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: New Alibaba AI framework skips loading every tool (VentureBeat, Jul 2)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"buttons\": [{\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-03-2\"}, \"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-03-2\"}, \"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\"}, {\"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-03-2\"}, \"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"style\": \"secondary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f4819697127149649b3dd9e5","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗢𝗻𝗹𝘆 𝟭 𝗶𝗻 𝟭𝟬 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗮𝗻𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵 𝗮 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\n\nLet that sink in.\n\n79% of enterprises have already paid for an agent going rogue.\nYet 90% can't automatically detect when it happens.\n\nWe're deploying AI faster than we're building guardrails.\nEvery company wants autonomous agents.\nAlmost none have autonomous monitoring.\n\nThe Morgan Stanley playbook I saw yesterday:\n- Human sign-off on every decision\n- Fixed rules, not probabilistic guesses\n- Zero room for error = zero autonomy\n\nThat's not backwards.\nThat's production-ready.\n\nThe companies winning with AI agents aren't the ones with the most autonomy.\nThey're the ones with the most observability.\n\nIf your AI agent fails at 3am on a Saturday —\nhow long until you know?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Production #Monitoring #EnterpriseAI\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Enterprises lost Claude Fable 5 for a few weeks (VentureBeat, Jul 3)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"buttons":[{"action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief